<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-15T15:04:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-15T15:04:00-05:00" n="1578" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1578">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/52.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Chihtiahua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-15T13:00:00-07:04">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s April 14, 5 p.m. Constitutionalist Secretary Foreign
                                Affairs Fabela has replied verbally that consistently with
                                principles already enunciated his government can not accept our
                                mediation in Radke’s case because of the fact that there is at
                                Chihuahua German Consular Officer through whom such representations
                                should be made to Carranza. He calls attention in this connection to
                                notes already sent to the Department through Carothers and
                                    Simpich.<note n="151" xml:id="d1578fn151">See, under Protection
                                    of Spanish subjects, Mr. Simpich’s No. 289 of Feb. 19; Mr.
                                    Carothers’s Apr. 9, 7 p.m.; Apr. 11, 7 p.m.: Apr. 12, and Apr.
                                    14; under Protection of British subjects, Mr. Simpich’s Feb. 26,
                                    Feb. 28, and Mar. 11.</note> Fabela states, however, that he
                                accepts the information and will act upon it as in any case brought
                                to attention by private parties.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>